records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 3 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 3 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 9 MONTHS probation.

  Conditions of Probation:
- 20 hours of community service
- Cooperate and testify truthfully about this case.
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation.
- No contact with the victims or co-actors named in the complaint.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  No Cash Bail Posted in this matter

Defendant changes her plea to NO CONTEST.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Jury trial date of 06/24/2015 is vacated.
